        section(data-background-size="contain") 
          h2 React
          p React is just the V
          p &ldquo; We built React to solve one problem: building large applications with data that changes over time. To do this, React uses two main ideas. &rdquo;

        section(data-background-size="contain") 
          h3 Simple
          p Simply express how your app should look at any given point in time, and React will automatically manage all UI updates when your underlying data changes.

        section(data-background-size="contain") 
          h3 Declarative
          p When the data changes, React conceptually hits the "refresh" button, and knows to only update the changed parts.

        section(data-background-size="contain") 
          h2 React Overview
          h3 View Only
          ol Notable Features
            li Virtual Dom 
            li Server Rendering
            li Descriptive Warning Messages
            li Custom Event System
            li Immutability Instead Of Observing
            li Etc.

        section(data-background-size="contain") 
          h2 React History
          ul
            li Born out of frustration with "cascading updates" and long ramp up times
            li Initially prototype by Jordan Walke, used ideas from XHP (internal PHP tool)
            li Used internally but tightly integrated into their codebase
            li After Instagram acquired, Pete Hunt did work of breaking it out into it's own library to build Instagram apps, open sourced it 2013

