        section(data-background-size="contain")
          h2 Future
          a(href="https://github.com/reactjs/react-future") React Future
          br
          p React is still growing and is very young.  It's too early to tell if future breaking changes are coming down the pipe.  Working on compiling React to native (Facebook Paper).

          a(href="http://eisenbergeffect.bluespire.com/all-about-angular-2-0/") Angular Future
          br
          p Angular, we know for sure that Angular 2 is a complete rewrite with no clear migration path.  Controllers have been removed, there is a new language called AtScript which they highly recommend in lieu of JavaScript, as well as many other breaking things.

        section(data-background-size="contain")
          h2 Summary
          h3 Angular
          p Angular is a full featured MVC Framework.  Angular tries and solve all the things for you, and if you do everything the Angular way, things work.
          h3 React
          p React is only the view layer, but it does this very well, cleanly and fast.  The core building block behind React are self-contained components.  React makes recommendations on how to build the application, but makes no requirements.

